⚖️ The grounded version (important balance)

Comparison isn’t inherently bad—it has two modes:

❌ Destructive comparison

* “I’m behind”
* “They’re better”
* identity-level judgment
* leads to anxiety, envy, paralysis

✅ Constructive comparison

* “What are they doing that works?”
* “What can I learn or adapt?”
* focused on process, not identity

